Whereas in severe cases of sepsis, a patient can experience a drop in blood pressure, a weakened
			 heart, and septic shock, causing potentially fatal  multiple organ
			 failure;

Whereas according to the Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality, sepsis is the most expensive
			 cause of hospitalization in the United States, with an annual cost of
			 $24,000,000,000;

Whereas an article in the Journal of the American Medical Association reports that more than 80
			 percent of individuals who die from sepsis arrive at the hospital with
			 sepsis;
